  "description": "The FIFA series receives its only entry on the Game Boy Color with <i>FIFA 2000</i>. The game is very similar to developer Tiertex' earlier <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/gameboy/fifa-soccer-97\">entries</a> <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/gameboy/fifa-road-to-world-cup-98\">in the</a> <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/gameboy/world-cup-98_\">series</a>, with the same isometric graphics (updated for the GBC's capabilities) and many similar options and modes.<br><br>It features the traditional exhibition, tournament, playoffs and league modes and adds a new mode for indoor games. Also new is a quick start option for a quick random game. There are 63 teams available (up from 52 in the predecessors) - 62 national squads plus the THQ Tornados all-star team.",
